definitions.definition: A hollow place in the earth; an abyss ; a deep chasm or basin .
That which swallows irretrievably; a whirlpool ; a sucking eddy .
A portion of an ocean or sea extending into the land; a partially landlocked sea
A large deposit of ore in a lode .
A wide interval or gap; a separating space.
A difference, especially a large difference, between groups.
The bottom part of a list of those awarded a degree, for those who have only just passed.

main_definition: A hollow place in the earth; an abyss ; a deep chasm or basin .
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete ) That which swallows; the gullet .

( mining ) A large deposit of ore in a lode .
( figurative ) A wide interval or gap; a separating space.
( figurative ) A difference, especially a large difference, between groups.
( Oxbridge slang ) The bottom part of a list of those awarded a degree, for those who have only just passed.
